metadata.name: Annum #6360
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: [fxhashturnsone] 2022 A Generative Odyssey #245
metadata.description:
ü™êüåå‚ú®

2022 A Generative Odyssey (Story of a traveler)

A simple space landscape generator üèû
Allows some exploration for curious ones üì°
Don't forget to press "4" to take a panoramic picture üì∏ü§≥

üï≥üß≠üõ∞



-----
* Technics *

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Pure code / no external assets
- Interactive / orbitable
- 8 scenes with unlimited possible variations
- 5 capture / screenshot modes 8K+

-----
* Controls *

Left click / touch + drag : orbit around center of interest
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

Keyboard "1" : PNG capture the current view at same resolution / ratio 
Keyboard "2" : PNG capture view as square 4320x4320
Keyboard "3" : PNG capture at best resolution 8K (7680x4320)
Keyboard "4" : PNG capture as panoramic view (8192x2304)
Keyboard "5" : PNG capture as super-panoramic (10650x3000)

-----
* URL modifier *

"&r=1"
enables auto rotation of view (equivalent to "R" key press)

-----
* Mint details *

- Mint preview / capture is PNG 1920x1920

-----
@HAL09999 ‚Äì May/November 2022

metadata.name: BRTLSMBRTHDY #337
metadata.description:
Happy Brutalist birthday fxhash! A little Work In Progress turned into a quick sketch. Enjoy your ghost buildings.

All primary profits go to the Processing Foundation.

INSTRUCTIONS ::

(all of these will take a few moments)
h - Toggle high-res
t - toggle paper texture off
s - Download and save image

PRINTING INSTRUCTIONS ::

High-res will output a 8,192 x 8,192 image, at 300dpi it should print at...

27.3 x 27.3 inches
69.3 x 69.3 cm

metadata.name: Spheara #318
metadata.description:
Third in a series exploring abstract expressionism by painting noise fields.

Released as part of the Fx(hash) turns one event (#fxhashturnsone) in November 2022. Thank you for the amazing year!

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a screenshot. Image size is 2053x3000px
Press ‚Äôp‚Äô to pause/resume.

metadata.name: 365 Tentacles #339
metadata.description:
Wow, Fxhash ! What a year !

For #fxhashturnsone I decided to explore how far I could take a simple concept: drawing 365 tentacles.
This turned out to be an interesting exercise, as having a strict limitation seemed to spark more ideas than when having complete freedom. There's a lot you can do with 365 things !

99.9% of primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Key commands:
's' to save a png image
'1', '2', '4' to change resolution
'+', '-' to change rendering zoom

metadata.name: SuperCube 1000 #375
metadata.description:
Celebrating 1000 projects on fxhash by releasing 1000 unique editions for free.

This is a tribute to Victor Vasarely (1906-1997), whom I consider to be one of the fathers of the generative art movement, and whose art was very present in the house I grew up in as a child.

metadata.name: Appropriate Hidden Breeze #178
metadata.description:
"Appropriate Hidden Breeze" is a study of blending gradients on a grid. 

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size 12x12" @ 300 DPI
